To earn points please navigate to `Project -> Subject -> Skill -> Metrics`.

The Skill Metrics page depicts several metrics and charts including:

* **Achieved** \- Number of users that achieved this skill
* **In Progress** \- Number of Users with some points earned toward the skill
* **Last Achieved** \- The last time the skill was achieved by a user
* **Achievements over time chart** \- number of total users that achieved this skill plotted over time
* **Skill events time-chart** \- shows the number of reported and applied events over time
    * Only 'applied' events contribute to users' points and achievements.
    * An event will not be applied if that skill has already reached its maximum points or has unfulfilled dependencies.

![image.png](data:image/png;base64,)

### Post Achievement Metrics

These metrics are applicable to any application that integrated SkillTree gamified training by instrumenting its code to report skill events when skills are preformed within that tool/application (and optionally embedding Ranking and Visualization views). Post Achievement Metrics is then a critical tool to gain insight to whether users continue to utilize the feature after fully achieving the skill.

![image.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Post Achievement Metrics include:

* **User Counts** \- \# of users that continued using the skill ***vs*** # of users that stopped after achieving it
* **Usage** \- for users that did achieve the skill the breakdown in the amount of usage from very little to a lot
    * Each item depicts the number of times this Skill is performed per user after having fully achieved it
* **Users that Achieved this Skill** \- Tabular display of users that achieved the skill with a switch between `Still Using` users vs. `Stopped` users.
